[h1]Vigil at the Holy Site[/h1]

Devote yourself to your faith, and offer up a captive to seal the rite.

[h2]The Vigil[/h2]
A once-per-game player decision, unfolding across three screens.

[list]
[*] Choose your officiant: yourself (stress), your court chaplain (50 gold to them; stress for the greedy), or a captured priest of a hostile faith (chance to gain sadistic or arbitrary; stress relief if you already are).
[*] Pick the captive, or choose between two. 5000 piety and a faith-flavored end: Norse harrow, Christian pyre, Islamic blade, Tengri peak, or generic altar.
[*] Read the omens. The officiant's Learning weights a four-tier contest from blessed (5y modifier, faith fervor +3, reveal a murder scheme on you) to dark (3y modifier, paranoid risk on the officiant).
[/list]

[h2]Burn the Infidel Holy Place[/h2]
After the Vigil, a second decision unlocks. While your army stands on a holy site of another faith you hold by right, by siege, or have just raided, you may desecrate it. 5000 piety; the county carries Desecrated Ground (-100% tax, -50% levy) for 80 years.

[h2]Consequences of the desecration[/h2]
The harmed faith takes notice. From your vassals and neighboring rulers of that faith, existing rivals preferred:
[list]
[*] The most cunning becomes your rival and starts a murder scheme on you.
[*] The strongest landed becomes your rival and declares a Punitive War. Wargoal: your captivity. If the holy place lay inside your own realm, the war also strips its de jure duchy on your defeat.
[*] One character may take both roles.
[/list]

[h2]Compatibility[/h2]
CK3 1.19. Adds decisions, events, a custom casus belli, and county/character modifiers. Does not edit vanilla files.
